{"parse":{"title":"2012 Sahel drought","pageid":36096878,"revid":856085459,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Future_droughts_of_the_Sahel_Region\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Future droughts of the Sahel Region</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Societal_impacts\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Societal impacts</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Mass_Famine\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Mass Famine</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Future_droughts_of_the_Sahel_Region\">Future droughts of the Sahel Region</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=2012_Sahel_drought&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Future droughts of the Sahel Region\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2><p>\nThe droughts are becoming increasingly more common, worse and more threatening due to <a href=\"/wiki/Global_warming\" title=\"Global warming\">global warming</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-:2_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:2-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> A possible explanation to the aridity trend is the supplements of an oceanography phenomenon called <a href=\"/wiki/El_Ni%C3%B1o\" title=\"El Ni\u00f1o\">El Ni\u00f1o</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-:2_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:2-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> An idea is that evaporation is occurring at higher rate due to the change in <a href=\"/wiki/Sea_surface_temperature\" title=\"Sea surface temperature\">Sea surface temperature</a>, this then impacts the amount of rain the <a href=\"/wiki/Sahel\" title=\"Sahel\">Sahel</a> region receives<sup id=\"cite_ref-:2_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:2-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Another factor to keep into consideration is the response of our atmosphere to stimulants like greenhouse gases and carbon emissions.<sup id=\"cite_ref-:2_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:2-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Sahel_Map-Africa_rough.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d1/Sahel_Map-Africa_rough.png/300px-Sahel_Map-Africa_rough.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"139\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d1/Sahel_Map-Africa_rough.png/450px-Sahel_Map-Africa_rough.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d1/Sahel_Map-Africa_rough.png/600px-Sahel_Map-Africa_rough.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"2000\" data-file-height=\"925\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Sahel_Map-Africa_rough.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The Sahel region \u2013 a belt up to 1,000 km wide that spans Africa from the <a href=\"/wiki/Atlantic_Ocean\" title=\"Atlantic Ocean\">Atlantic Ocean</a> to the <a href=\"/wiki/Red_Sea\" title=\"Red Sea\">Red Sea</a></div></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Societal_impacts\">Societal impacts</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=2012_Sahel_drought&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Societal impacts\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Mass_Famine\">Mass Famine</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=2012_Sahel_drought&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Mass Famine\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p><a href=\"/wiki/Valerie_Amos,_Baroness_Amos\" title=\"Valerie Amos, Baroness Amos\">Valerie Amos</a>, UN Humanitarian Chief during 2012, released a statement during the year stating that over 15 million people were malnourished in West Africa and the <a href=\"/wiki/Sahel\" title=\"Sahel\">Sahel</a> region.<sup id=\"cite_ref-:0_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:0-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>  The main contributor to the famine was the drought of Sahel, ensued from a combination of failing crops and <a href=\"/wiki/El_Ni%C3%B1o\" title=\"El Ni\u00f1o\">El Ni\u00f1o</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-:2_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:2-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/wiki/Mauritania\" title=\"Mauritania\">Mauritania</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Chad\" title=\"Chad\">Chad</a> recorded a loss in crop yield of over 50% when compared to 2011. Food reserves in the areas affected were very low and combined with corn prices soaring by 60-85% compared to averages over the last five years. In Chad alone this food crisis affected some 3.6 million people.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> In places like <a href=\"/wiki/Burkina_Faso\" title=\"Burkina Faso\">Burkina Faso</a> over 2.8 million were suffering from famine and in Senegal over 800,000 did not have enough to eat.<sup id=\"cite_ref-:0_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:0-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=2012_Sahel_drought&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>FAO, <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.fao.org/crisis/sahel/\">the 2012 Sahel Crisis</a></i></li>\n<li>SOS Children 2012, <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.soschildrensvillages.org.uk/charity-news/sahel-emergency-appeal-2012\">Sahel drought</a></i></li>\n<li>The Guardians Poverty Matters Blog May 2012, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/poverty-matters/2012/may/25/baaba-maal-sahel-food-water\">Baaba Maal: people in the Sahel region need food and water now</a></li>\n<li>ABC News, May 2012, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/18-million-west-africa-hungry-2012-16449498#.T9R2EcVKSFE\">UN: 18 Million in West Africa to Go Hungry in 2012</a></li>\n<li>CNN, June 2012, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://edition.cnn.com/2012/06/05/world/africa/sahel-hunger/index.html\">A distress call from Africa's Sahel: Millions might starve</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=2012_Sahel_drought&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-:2-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-:2_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=